phlagrant command list
-------------------------
ssh-config   outputs OpenSSH valid configuration to connect to the machine
 - get machine connect details from papyrus-local (papyrus commit/push papyrus-local dont)
 - display the details
 - 1 day






DONE
------------------

ssh DONE auto-ssh cli
connects to machine via SSH
             invoke ssh using the ssh params configured during phlagrant up and put into local-papyrus
 - get machine connect details from papyrus-local (papyrus commit/push papyrus-local dont)
 - get id from name
 - invokessh with these details
 - 1/2 days

package      packages a running vagrant environment into a box
THIS WILL BECOME BOX PACKAGE

box DONE box add, box remove
    add - manages boxes: installation, removal, etc. download/install/remove a base box

provision DONE phlagrant provision now
    now -provisions the vagrant machine, install pharoah and execute pharoah autopilots
reload  DONE phlagrant up reload
    restarts vagrant machine, loads new Vagrantfile configuration

status  DONE phlagrant status full, show
    phlagrant status full     outputs status of the vagrant machine
    phlagrant status show     outputs status of the vagrant machine

destroy DONE phlagrant destroy now
    phlagrant destroy now, stops and deletes all traces of the vagrant machine

halt DONE stops the vagrant machine
    phlagrant halt hard, stops with hard power button
    phlagrant halt now, stops with ssh shutdown, then soft power button, then hard power button

help DONE shows the help for a subcommand
    phlagrant *MODULE* help

init DONE is flirt (or init works too, if you must)
    phlagrant flirt now  initializes a new Vagrant environment by creating a Vagrantfile

resume DONE phlagrant resume now
    phlagrant resume now, resume a suspended vagrant machine, resume the box described in papyruslocal

suspend DONE - THIS IS NOW HALT SUSPEND/PAUSE
   phlagrant halt suspend, suspends the machine
   phlagrant halt pause, suspends the machine

up     DONE -
   phlagrant up now --modify --provision, starts, modifies hardware of and provisions the vagrant environment






